sectioned_description.description:
We invite you to discover our spacious and sunny studio of 38m2, recently renovated and decorated, with a great south facing garden view.  It's cute and cozy, perfect for two, we're sure you'll love it!
A free library (in english and french) is at your disposal, don't hesitate to swap or take one!
In the heart of town, in a calm historic building, it's the perfect place to discover Evian on foot!
Free parking closeby or underground parking next to studio.
Sheets, towels and wifi provided.

Entirely renovated and decorated by ourselves, you'll find all the home amenities to make your stay comfortable!
The cosy bedroom is seperated from the living room by a large glass wall, with a double bed  (140x190cm), a desk space for work, and a large dressing room.
The kitchen is complete with a stove, oven microwave, coffee machine, toaster, electric kettle and a fridge/freezer.  
You'll love the large bathroom with shower, where you'll also find a washing machine at your disposal.

The living room has a great view of the garden, which is nicely flowered in the summer.  As the windows face south, you'll get lots of sunlight, even in winter!  You'll be able to relax by using the WIFI internet, watching TV, using the DVD player or reading one of the many books at your disposal!

The bed is made for your arrival and the towels are included (bath towels and tea towels).  You'll find basic kitchen ammenities such as salt, spices, coffee, tea, sugar...

The studio is on the 2nd floor but you have easy access from the south entrance (nearest the parking) which is on the same floor.
Public underground parking (0,60€/hour) and free parking (4 hours with a disk) are nearby.

The entrance to the studio is fully autonomous and secured with a lock box. 
You have access to the entire studio.  However the terrasse in the garden is for the view only!

You can always reach us by telephone or email.

You are in the historical center of Evian, right on the main pedestrian street.  The historical building dates from 1650, and is where the castle of Evian once stood.  You can still see two towers from the garden!  
It's the perfect place from which to discover the city by foot, the Thermes Spa is only minutes away, as is the Evian water fountain, Lake Geneva and the ferry to Switzerland, shops, restaurants, transports...
Evian is a 15 min drive to the ski stations of Bernex and Thollon-les-memises.
We'll be glad to help you organise your stay, just ask!

We are centrally located and close to all transports:
Ferry to Lausanne: 5 min by foot
Train: 10 min by foot
Bus: 5 min by foot
Funiculaire: 2 min by foot
Bus to ski stations Bernex and Thollon: min by foot

Sheets and towels are included.  City tax included.  Basic kitchen ammenities included.  Thank you for leaving the studio clean.
